  • Deprecated Interfaces 
    Interface and Description
    org.jparsec.functors.Binary
    Use BinaryOperator instead.

    Use Function instead.

    org.jparsec.functors.Unary
    Use UnaryOperator instead.
  • Deprecated Classes 
    Class and Description
    org.jparsec.error.Location
    Prefer to use SourceLocation instead.
    org.jparsec.functors.Pair

    Prefer to using a lambda expression to convert to your own type.

    Prefer to using a lambda expression to convert to your own type.
  • Deprecated Fields 
    Field and Description
    org.jparsec.Parsers.INDEX
    Use Parsers.SOURCE_LOCATION instead.
    org.jparsec.functors.Maps.TO_INTEGER
    Use Integer::valueOf directly.
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.jparsec.Scanners.among(String, String)
    Use Patterns.among(chars).toScanner(name).
    org.jparsec.Terminals.caseInsensitive(Parser<String>, String[], String[])
    Use operators(ops) .words(wordScanner) .caseInsensitiveKeywords(keywords) .build() instead.
    org.jparsec.Terminals.caseInsensitive(Parser<String>, String[], String[], Function<String, ?>)
    Use operators(ops) .words(wordScanner) .tokenizeWordsWith(wordMap) .caseInsensitiveKeywords(keywords) .build() instead.
    org.jparsec.Terminals.caseInsensitive(String[], String[])
    Use operators(ops) .words(Scanners.IDENTIFIER) .caseInsensitiveKeywords(keywords) .build() instead.
    org.jparsec.Terminals.caseSensitive(Parser<String>, String[], String[])
    Use operators(ops) .words(wordScanner) .keywords(keywords) .build() instead.
    org.jparsec.Terminals.caseSensitive(Parser<String>, String[], String[], Function<String, ?>)
    Use operators(ops) .words(wordScanner) .tokenizeWordsWith(wordMap) .keywords(keywords) .build() instead.
    org.jparsec.Terminals.caseSensitive(String[], String[])
    Use operators(ops) .words(Scanners.IDENTIFIER) .keywords(keywords) .build() instead.
    org.jparsec.functors.Maps.constant(T)
    Use from -> to directly.
    org.jparsec.error.ParserException.getLocation()
    Use ParserException.getLine() and ParserException.getColumn() instead.
    org.jparsec.error.ParserException.getModuleName()
    org.jparsec.functors.Maps.identity()
    Use Function.identity() instead.
    org.jparsec.Scanners.isChar(CharPredicate, String)
    Implement Object.toString() in the CharPredicate, or use Patterns.isChar(predicate).toScanner(name).
    org.jparsec.Scanners.isChar(char, String)
    Use Scanners.isChar(char) instead or use Patterns.isChar(ch).toScanner(name).
    org.jparsec.pattern.Pattern.many(int)
    Use Pattern.atLeast(int) instead.
    org.jparsec.pattern.Patterns.many(int, CharPredicate)
    Use Patterns.atLeast(int, CharPredicate) instead.
    org.jparsec.Scanners.many(Pattern, String)
    Use pattern.many().toScanner(name).
    org.jparsec.Scanners.many1(Pattern, String)
    Use pattern.many1().toScanner(name).
    org.jparsec.functors.Maps.map(Map<K, V>)
    Use Map::get instead.
    org.jparsec.functors.Maps.mapToString()
    Use String::valueOf directly.
    org.jparsec.Scanners.notAmong(String, String)
    Use Patterns.among(chars).not().toScanner(name), or isChar(CharPredicates.notAmong(chars), name).
    org.jparsec.Scanners.notChar(char, String)
    Use Scanners.notChar(char).
    org.jparsec.Parser.optional()
    since 3.0. Use #optional(null) or Parser.asOptional() instead.
    org.jparsec.Parsers.pair(Parser<? extends A>, Parser<? extends B>)
    Prefer to converting to your own object with a lambda.
    org.jparsec.Parser.parse(CharSequence, String)
    Please use Parser.parse(CharSequence) instead.
    org.jparsec.Parser.parse(Readable, String)
    Please use Parser.parse(Readable) instead.
    org.jparsec.Scanners.pattern(Pattern, String)
    Use pattern.toScanner(name).
    org.jparsec.Scanners.quoted(Parser<Void>, Parser<Void>, Parser<?>)
    Use Parsers.sequence(begin, quoted.skipMany(), end).source().
    org.jparsec.Parser.reluctantBetween(Parser<?>, Parser<?>)
    This method probably only works in the simplest cases. And it's a character-level parser only. Use it at your own risk. It may be deleted later when we find a better way.
    org.jparsec.pattern.Pattern.repeat(int)
    Use Pattern.times(int) instead.
    org.jparsec.Parsers.runnable(Runnable)
    org.jparsec.pattern.Pattern.some(int)
    Use Pattern.atMost(int) instead.
    org.jparsec.pattern.Patterns.some(int, CharPredicate)
    Use Patterns.atMost(int, CharPredicate) instead.
    org.jparsec.pattern.Pattern.some(int, int)
    Use Pattern.times(int, int) instead.
    org.jparsec.pattern.Patterns.some(int, int, CharPredicate)
    Use Patterns.times(int, int, CharPredicate) instead.
    org.jparsec.Scanners.string(String, String)
    Use Patterns.string(str).toScanner(name).
    org.jparsec.Scanners.stringCaseInsensitive(String, String)
    Use Patterns.stringCaseInsensitive(str).toScanner(name).
    org.jparsec.functors.Maps.toTuple3()
    org.jparsec.functors.Maps.toTuple4()
    org.jparsec.functors.Maps.toTuple5()
    org.jparsec.Parsers.tuple(Parser<? extends A>, Parser<? extends B>)
    Prefer to converting to your own object with a lambda.
    org.jparsec.Parsers.tuple(Parser<? extends A>, Parser<? extends B>, Parser<? extends C>)
    Prefer to converting to your own object with a lambda.
    org.jparsec.Parsers.tuple(Parser<? extends A>, Parser<? extends B>, Parser<? extends C>, Parser<? extends D>)
    Prefer to converting to your own object with a lambda.
    org.jparsec.Parsers.tuple(Parser<? extends A>, Parser<? extends B>, Parser<? extends C>, Parser<? extends D>, Parser<? extends E>)
    Prefer to converting to your own object with a lambda.
